condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 PA 3(a) | Description: establish and thereafter maintain a State Water Resources Agency to be headedby a suitably qualified and experienced person, to be the state-wide focal agency for WRM in a river basin context. | Due Date:31-Dec-2005

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 PA 3(b) | Description: establish and thereafter maintain a SWARDAC to be the focal point to collate,verify, analyze and disseminate information needed for IWRM and basin planning. | Due Date: 31-Dec-2005

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 PA 3(c) | Description: prepare and submit for consideration for adoption appropriate draft enablinglegislation for the establishment and operationalization of a SWaTReC. | Due Date: 30-Jun-2015

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 PA 3(d) | Description: establish and thereafter maintain on a pilot basis the SBDMB and TBDMB tooperationalize the IWRM concept in a decentralized basin development and management framework. | Due Date :31-Dec-2005
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 PA 4 | Description: installation and testing of computer systems and communication infrastructure(WAn/LAN) for both data and voice | Due Date :31-Dec-2005

title.narrative: Area provided with irrigation and drainage services - New (ha)
Number of schemes with improved fish production in reservoirs and ponds
Number of systems where performance management targets established and being met by system managers.
Number of schemes with agricultural intensification and diversification
Number of systems ready to supply the planned volumes of water at specified delivery points

Irrigation service delivery by service providers (WRD and WUAs) assessed as satisfactory or above by at least 60 per cent of water users in the schemes that are already completed or where works are on
Water users provided with irrigation and drainage services - female (number)
Operational water user associations created and/or strengthened (number)
Area provided with irrigation and drainage services (ha)
Area provided with irrigation and drainage services - Improved (ha)
Water users provided with new/improved irrigation and drainage services (number)
Targeted families with increased incomes (measured in %)
Increased crop production per unit of water delivered (measured in kg per cubic meter of water).
Average fish production productivity in reservoirs (measured in kg per ha of water spread area)
Average farm income of project beneficiaries (measured in Rs. per ha).
Average fish productivity in village ponds (measured in kg per ha of water spread area)
Single State water governance body established and functioning in accordance with stated roles and responsibilities

baseline.value: No arrangements in place, with fragmented management of water resources.

target.value: Single State water governance body established and functioning in accordance with stated roles and responsibilities(WRM Wing, withSWaRA and SWaDRAC incorporated).

actual.value: WRM Wing has been formed and functioning with returned WRM trainees/specialists. Draft comprehensive, modern river basin plansprepared and reviewed by WRD. WRM Wing specialists now using modern tools for river basin planning and management.
